author: @zakcodes3507
text: The reason why tensorflow can't just load a model is because it only saves the weights and doesn't save the structure. Essentially in your weight file you only got one big list of doubles. I do agree that it is cool to be able to load the model without defining it but in most applications you're either creating a new model or loading it so you have to know the structure of your model so you shouldn't have to save the structure.
